{
  "stem": "3771.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And physically, it was impossible to survive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Was-- was mentally.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "That he-- every day, he said, 'The war will come to an end.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "You have to hold on to it, and hold on to it.' And finally, he got me into such a point that I was, well, if I shall die, I will die at least a free man.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And actually, I called myself after the war-- when I spoke in many-- I called myself the one which got away.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I said, Hitler didn't want that I should be standing here, in front of you in this auditorium, with so many people of you, for the armed forces, that I should stand here and expose the horrifying suffering, the horrendous thing with the humiliation.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "What this-- those people have actually put on-- on those victimized people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "He didn't want me I should tell you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And I-- somehow I [INAUDIBLE] I said, I call myself, the one which got away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, actually, after-- I had a number of friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- from the beginning, I was much stronger.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to get at night-- even in dark, we will sit together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would read for him poetry, and I would tell him things of human behavior, that you can lift yourself up above your physical needs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because, actually, what keeps you going is your mind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Don't let your mind die on you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If you let your mind die-- because your mind is the-- the main-- what do you call it-- the which directs your life, from walking, to speaking, to do anythings.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Once your mind loses-- you lose it, your body is finished.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even at this, a bag of bones, but your mind keep on saying it to you, you can do it.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
